It is difficult to determine which college wrestler has won the most matches as it depends on the time period and weight class considered. However, some of the most successful college wrestlers in recent history include:

* Cael Sanderson, Penn State University (159-0 record)
* Kyle Dake, Cornell University (136-4 record)
* Pat Smith, Oklahoma State University (127-10 record)
* Logan Stieber, Ohio State University (133-3 record)
* Jordan Burroughs, University of Nebraska (159-6 record)

These wrestlers are considered among the best in college wrestling history and have won numerous national championships and accolades during their college careers.
